This project was to build and validated a multiple regression model to identify physicochemical factors affecting wine quality ratings. 
• Cleaned dataset and sampled 300 observations; addressed collinearity (free vs. total SO₂) and selected an 8-variable model 
using forward stepwise selection with AIC, adjusted R², and MSE.
• Evaluated model assumptions and outliers using residual plots, Q–Q plots, leverage, Cook’s distance, and jackknife diagnostics.
• Performed coincidence and parallelism tests showing wine color modifies predictor effects; alcohol and sulphates increased 
quality while density reduced it.
